  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for church-led peacebuilding in South Sudan 2020-2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Planned Activities:
- Support for locally led peace Initiatives/ICCs Implementation of the APP
- Conduct workshop Orientation to returnees and people living in POCs on the importance of reconciliation peaceful Co-existence 1 in Jonglei and Upper Nile. 
- Establishment and Formation of women and youth link for peace (Renk and Maban)
- Conduct annual conference for women link/women church leaders for peace (Greater Upper Nile region in Malakal)
- Awareness raising workshop on trauma Healing  to women and youth (Malakal, Jonglei &amp; Renk town)
- Conduct regular anti-hate speech training workshop to church leaders, local authorities, and clergy. 
- Support Supervision Visits for project activities by SSCC &amp; CTP</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The church in South Sudan is effectively addressing conflict at multiple levels and is making a significant contribution towards building sustainable national peace in South Sudan.</narrative>
  </description>
